<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 92 / Inquiry into medical fees: Senior figure to head team
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR PETER DEAN, a deputy chairman of the Monopolies and Mergers Commission,
will chair the inquiry into the supply of private medical services.
Mr Dean, aged 53, is a freelance business consultant and was an executive
director of RTZ, the mining group, from 1974 to 1985.
He is a solicitor and a non-executive director of Associated British Ports
Holdings and Liberty Life Assurance Company.
He became a member of the MMC in 1982 and was also a member of the British
Transport Docks Board in 1980-82. His recreations in Who's Who are listed as
choral singing and skiing.
He was unable to comment on his appointment yesterday because he was
recovering from an eye operation.
A further group of between three and six people will be chosen later this
week to run the investigation.
They will gather written information, and also invite oral representation to
a series of hearings.
