</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Christian Democrat leadership has decided to send a senior
representative to Reggio Calabria to assess the consequences of the arrest
of 12 of its leading members on alleged corruption charges on Monday, writes
Robert Graham in Rome.
Those arrested include four ex-mayors of the southern city and two Christian
