FT  08 SEP 92 / The TUC At Blackpool: Unions to open base in Brussels
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART, Labour Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE TUC is to open an office in Brussels. Mr Bill Jordan, leader of the AEEU
craft union, said yesterday the office would be cost-effective as unions did
much business with the European Commission.
Mr Jordan, launching a TUC 'Network Europe' to improve union contacts within
the EC, said he was proposing a common European union card for members of
engineering and metalworking unions, though he advised against interpreting
such a move as the first step towards pan-European unionism.
The problem of fostering co-operation across borders between unions with
different bargaining cultures continues to prevent the establishment of a
European works council at Ford. The German union I G Metall insists that
only Ford employees can be on the council while the UK unions insist that
full-time union officials must also have a voice.
