</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SEVEN MEMBERS of the new premier league, the top English football division,
walked out of a meeting of the clubs yesterday after a Pounds 13m
sponsorship deal with Bass, the brewer, had been blocked.
Eight of the league's 22 clubs had voted against accepting the deal because
they felt it might conflict with their own sponsorships by brewers.
The seven clubs which walked out argued that the action by the eight was
against the interests of the Premier League as a whole.
Fourteen clubs voted to accept the deal - one less than the 15 votes needed
to carry the motion.
