Leading shares pared earlier gains on news that Ciskei soldiers had opened
fire on ANC supporters, killing 14 people. Industrials fell 9 to 4,102 and
the overall index was off 4 at 3,178. But golds rose 8 to 943 on the back of
the firmer bullion price.
