Sweden's large packaging company, will step down as chief executive when the
company joins operations with Alfa-Laval on January 1 1993, Reuter reports
from Stockholm. He will remain chairman of the group.
Mr Lars Hallden, president of the Alfa-Laval group, is appointed new chief
executive to the group, named Tetra Laval Group. The group will have a
combined turnover of Dollars 8.5bn in 1992. Tetra Pak bought dairy and food
processing group Alfa-Laval in 1991 for Dollars 2.5bn. The two have been
operating separately pending a decision to merge operations.
