FT  07 SEP 92 / International Company News: Three join Yangpu project
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
KUMAGAI GUMI (Hong Kong) has signed up Citic, the Bank of China and Mr Li
Ka-shing's Cheung Kong group, among its partners for the HKDollars 18bn
(USDollars 2.33bn) development of the Yangpu free port zone in Hainan
Island, China.
