</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE ANNUAL meeting of GEC was told that sales in the current year were
marginally down but profits were slightly higher compared with a year ago.
Lord Prior, chairman, said the principal businesses - electronics systems,
power systems and telecommunications - were maintaining high order books and
benefiting from the restructuring measures taken earlier.
