wish; market conditions are not improving, and further action will be
taken.'
The policy of requiring profits to show in cash had led to increases in bank
balances with consequent higher interest income.
Last week Yarrow Shipbuilders, a subsidiary, announced that it was to cut
510 jobs because of a gap in its order book. Last year, GEC shed about 5,000
staff in a restructuring of its defence activities.
